Directions: in a bowl , combine 1 can of red ale , sugar , and 1 / 2 stick of the butter and mix well
add berries
sift together flour , salt , baking powder , and cumin
with a fork gently work in to flour mixture with your hands until all of the flour is incorporated
in a large mixing bowl , combine 2 cups of blueberries , 2 1 / 2 cup red ale , and 2 / 3 cup strawberries
beat with a wooden spoon or two spooning in water until combined , adding more flour if needed
add flour mixture to blueberries / strawberries mix well
in a lightly greased 8x8x2 baking pan , layer the first three ingredients , followed by the third 2nd and third red ale mixture
bake at 375 for 14-16 minutes and then reduce heat to a simmer
